verbose_text: Based on stepwise multiple logistic regression analysis of factors (Child-Pugh classification, creatinine, EMP-ap (CD31 + CD42b - AN-V +), NO metabolites, and VEGF), VEGF level [odds ratio (OR) : 11.593, 95% confidence interval (CI) : 3.742-16.024, p < 0.007] and plasma EMP-ap level (OR : 6.285, 95% CI : 3.837-8.887, p < 0.001) were found to be independent predictors of ascites formation (XREF_TABLE).
